Top 5 Things That Will Break You Right Now
1. P0 Bug: builder.py has two build_graph() functions (lines 107 and 290)
Python uses the last definition. The second one has no MemorySaver, no interrupt_before declarations. This means checkpointing is silently disabled and the approval gate doesn't work. Every session loses state on restart. This is a one-line delete to fix — remove everything from line 262 to end of file.
2. GitHub Service commits the wrong thing
The full implementation that actually modifies locals.tf exists and is good — but dead POC code is still present that commits only a .copilot/glue-job-patches/*.md description file instead of real Terraform. Confusing to anyone reading the code and risky if the wrong branch gets executed.
3. No authentication on WebSocket
Anyone who knows the URL ws://your-server/ws/{session_id} can create PRs to your Terraform repo. Zero auth, zero authz.
4. In-memory only sessions
MemorySaver stores all state in RAM. Any server restart wipes all active sessions. Scale to 2 servers and sessions don't transfer. Replace with SqliteSaver for dev (1-line change) or Redis for production.
5. Reconnect shows a blank screen
When a user refreshes the browser, the graph state is preserved but the UI shows nothing — history is not replayed. Users will think they lost their work.

